text:
She's making the most of her time away with her boyfriend.

And Kourtney Kardashian flaunted her fit figure while on a romantic date night with boyfriend Younes Bendjima in Rome on Wednesday evening.

The 39-year-old reality television personality was dressed to impress for dinner wearing a tight beige dress after leaving La Taverna Flavia restaurant.

Scroll down for video

Lovely: Kourtney Kardashian flaunted her fit figure while on a romantic date night with boyfriend Younes Bendjima in Rome on Wednesday evening

Kourtney's sweeping taupe dress was partially sleeveless, with a large piece of fabric draped across one shoulder.

The nearly-sheer number hugged her svelte waistline and billowed down to her toes, revealing a pair of black mesh mules.

She carried a black Fendi tote in one hand, with the brand's name plastered across the small purse.

The mother-of-three wore her raven-hued hair straight to her shoulders and dusted just a touch of highlighter onto her cheekbones.

Younes seemed at ease next to his lady love as he sported a black T-shirt with the Camel cigarette logo emblazoned on his chest and back.

The Algerian-born model sported a pair of black cargo pants, with black trainers laced to his feet.

Earlier in the week, Kourtney appeared to be on cloud nine trekking around town with Younes.

She has been documenting her recent trip on Instagram and snapped herself at the Trevi Fountain and the Spanish Steps.

In May, Kourtney celebrated her one-year anniversary with Younes, who she was first pictured with at the Cannes Film Festival.

Celebrating the milestone, the brunette beauty posted a snap of a bouquet of red roses, adding: '365 days of love,' tagging her beau - who is a boxer-turned-model from Algeria.

Previously, the reality star dated Scott Disick for nine years but split in late 2016 following a tumultuous relationship.
